race.comment: SAMARELLE (5) has made an excellent start to her career and looks set to continue that trend. Was strong through the line at Kembla Grange last time when narrowly denied and has been kept up to the mark with a quiet trial since. Blinkers go on to sharpen her and the inside gate gives her every chance to stalk the speed. Still learning but clearly talented. Expecting a bold showing. SNITZEL DANCER (3) also has early star quality, just missing at Rosehill when chasing gamely. Strips fitter, gets the right run, and the step up in trip looks ideal. Looms as the main danger. CHATTERLEY (6) continues to race well and looks ready to strike soon. Her trial since a tidy Newcastle return reads nicely, and McDonald's booking is a major tick. MILES OF GLORY (8) powered home to score at Kembla and still has upside, while PROFOUNDLY (2) is trending the right way and can feature with luck from the draw.
